name: second
definition: A second (symbol: s) is the base unit of time in the International System of Units (SI) and is the second division of the hour by sixty, the first division by 60 being the minute.

name: microsecond
definition: "A time unit which is equal to one millionth of a second or 10^[-6] s." [NIST:NIST]

name: millisecond
definition: "A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of a second or 10^[-3] s." [NIST:NIST]

name: nanosecond
definition: "A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a second or 10^[-9] s." [NIST:NIST]

name: picosecond
definition: "A time unit which is equal to 10^[-12] s." [NIST:NIST]

name: minute
definition: A minute is a period of 60 seconds.

name: hour
definition: An hour is a period of 60 minutes.

name: day
definition: A day is a period of 24 hours.

name: week
definition: A week is a period of 7 consecutive days.

name: month
definition: A month is a period of time that divides the year.

name: year
definition: A year is a period of time taken by a planet to make one revolution around the sun.

name: century
definition: A century is a period of one hundred years.

name: millennium
definition: A millenium is a period of 1000 years
